snippet.textDisplay:
The line "Jaunga kahan" becomes less of a question and more of a quiet vow: no matter where life takes us, my heart will always find its way back to you.

This kind of connection speaks of maturity—when love isn't possessive, but patient; when timing matters as much as feeling. It’s a hopeful pause, not a goodbye.
It's the kind of love that doesn’t demand, but waits; not a farewell, but a quiet intermission filled with hope.

snippet.textDisplay: It's 12.55 am Friday. This song has been on loop for the past one hour as i lay in my bed on a intense summer night. Its cuts so deep with every word yet i dare not change it. It has been two years since you disappeared into the thin air. Lying I'm not wondering, "Yaad hai mujhe teri har adaa, Muskuraahatein teri". I never looked at love that way, just clinging onto the tiniest of hopes, a hopes that one day when you'll back. How i won't have any word to explain what transpired in my heart and mind in this time. How I'll have Kaavish's words to tell you, "Jaaunga kahaan Main toh hoon yahaan, Tere dil ki aahatoon mein hoon" followed by the chorus on sadness.🥀

snippet.textDisplay: I'm In my college last semester, one month to go, there are few days then after I will never see her again  ,she's  junior(in 4th semester) , when she came in my college for the first time, and when I saw her for the first time I lost myself in her eyes, the purest feeling ,( I can't even explain ) , whenever I see her I feel alive, she is the reason I go college everyday, but she couldn't see my love  that I have for her, she got someone, he is her classmate, she's happy with him, everyday I see her with him, I always pretend it isn't effect me, but inside I know how much it hurts, the heartache, I can't do anything , I can't force her to choose me, what I can do is loving her silently, every night  at 2 am I listen to this song and start thinking about her, that makes me feel I love her in a way that no one can, what I did for her, the memories not with her, but  the ones which I make about her, the memories of ideas, dream I had about her, now I'm here thinking about her and tears felling down from my eyes 😊
